==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|candidātus||a person who is standing for public office}}, from {{m|la|candidus||dazzling white, shining, clear}} + {{m|la|-ātus||pos=an adjectival suffix}}, in reference to Roman candidates wearing bleached white togas as a symbol of purity at a public forum.

